    • Field Detail

      • K_COMPRESSION_LEVEL

        public static final String K_COMPRESSION_LEVEL

        The compression level. The greater the number, the more compression but the more CPU time is taken.

        The parameter name is "compressionLevel". The possible values are integers between 0 and 9 inclusive. The default is 5.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • K_FIXED_ENCODING

        public static final String K_FIXED_ENCODING

        Fixed Encoding value. This value is typically gzip / deflate. If this is set,the content encoding is fixed to the specified value and compression is only used if the user agent sends an accept-encoding header with the fixed value.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • K_INCLUDE_VARY

        public static final String K_INCLUDE_VARY

        Include Vary value. This value is used to indicate whether a vary header should be set in the response. This defaults to true and sends the vary header "Vary: Accept-Encoding".

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
